<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06052227 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06052227 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  SAN-JOSE; MAN; SEX-CRIME; POLICE; HUNT  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Call it the case of the missing dirty dancer.;    A &quot;good-looking, well-built&quot;man has appeared at various stores and a Los Altos junior high school,performing unsolicited stripteases. Police in San Jose, Pleasanton and othercities throughout the Bay Area want to catch his act.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  POLICE KEEP EYES PEELED FOR UNSOLICITED STRIPTEASER  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     In the latest of at least eight incidents, the unidentified man walked intoa Pleasanton women's clothing store, announced he was from a San Franciscomale stripping company and was going to strip to music for two femaleemployees of the store.;    &quot;He said it was a Valentine's Day present for us,&quot;said one of the employees, who asked not to be identified. &quot;He was a nicelooking young man, well-built and dressed in slacks, a shirt and a tie.&quot;;    The employees told the man he was at the wrong store. But he insisted, changedthe station on a nearby portable radio to a &quot;fast song,&quot; and stripped in frontof the women, exposing his penis and buttocks. The women protested and the manquickly put his clothes back on and ran out of the store.;     &quot;He was an OKdancer, I guess,&quot; the employee said. &quot;It looked more like wiggling.&quot;;    OnFeb. 1, the same man attempted to strip at a Pleasanton tanning salon. Thereceptionist immediately told him to stop, and he left the store withoutstripping, police said.;    Police say similar incidents have been reported inSan Jose, Mountain View, Palo Alto, Los Altos, Livermore and Moraga. The manalso appeared outside a Los Altos junior high school last December, where hestripped down to a G-string.;    Noreen Chorney, a Los Altos crime preventionofficer, said, &quot;He does the same thing everywhere he goes. He comes into abusiness, says he's a stripper from San Francisco and starts taking hisclothes off.&quot;;    The man is described as Anglo, 25 to 30 years old, about 6feet, muscular and weighing 170 to 210 pounds. There are few clues.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  FERNANDO QUINTERO, Mercury News Staff Writer  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  SAN JOSE MERCURY NEWS  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910221  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Thursday  </DAY><MONTH>  February  </MONTH><PG.COL>  1B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  329  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Thursday February 21, 199100052227,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>